Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Pamphylian pottery transport amphora at neck join to moderate turn. Clay near fine pink-buff; some mica. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 163, 19. Name Simias. Retrograde example, C. Brixhe, Timbres amphoriques de Pamphylie (Paris 2012) no. 381.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0074)
